In fact in Java there&#39;s a boolean operator called instanceof which can be used to determine if an object is an instance of a class, an instance of a subclass, or an instance of a class that implements a particular interface. 

    if(obj instanceof SomeClass) {
        // Do something
    }

The Java Tutorial has a [good example][1] of this operator


  [1]: http://java.sun.com/docs/books/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/examples/InstanceofDemo.java

[Class.isInstance][1] does what you want.

    if (Point.class.isInstance(someObj)){
        ...
    }


Of course, you shouldn&#39;t use it if you could use `instanceof` instead, but for reflection scenarios it often comes in handy.

  [1]: http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/lang/Class.html#isInstance(java.lang.Object)

